# Production-Grade V1 — Complete Wiring & Authenticity Plan

## Problem Statement

After a deep audit of the full codebase — all backend controllers, gateway routes, frontend API clients, pages, and stores — I've identified **3 categories of problems** preventing production readiness.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Build Step Dependency**: The `start_backend.ps1` script launches pre-built JAR files. Before the script can work, `mvn clean package -DskipTests` must be run. The plan adds this as a build step in the startup script. If you want manual Maven builds instead, let me know.

> [!WARNING]
> **Docker GPU Requirement**: The `docker-compose.yml` reserves an NVIDIA GPU for `ollama`. If your machine has no NVIDIA GPU, Docker will fail to start. The plan adds a fallback profile. Confirm if you have a GPU.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **cAdvisor Port Conflict**: `docker-compose.yml` maps cAdvisor's host port to `8085`, but that's also the Marketplace service port. This will cause a collision when both Docker and Marketplace run on the same machine. The plan remaps cAdvisor.

